adjectives.description: imprinted (comparative more imprinted, superlative most imprinted)

entries.meaning: (genetics) Produced by or exhibiting imprinting; showing distinction by its origin from the paternal or maternal genome.
examples: The inference is that there is an imprinted' gene somewhere on the X chromosome, which is normally switched on only on the paternal copy and that this gene somehow enhances the development of social adjustment [...].

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of imprint
